    <p class="lead">The Serials collection includes a wide range of dailies, weeklies, specialized journals and mass‑market magazines, as well as city directories and annual reports from churches, schools, and corporations.</p>
    <p>Specialized publications include trade or industry journals in addition to popular magazines catering to various demographics. Early periodicals provide invaluable insight into the ideas and opinions of their time, and richly illustrated journals open a captivating window onto early Canadian society through articles, advertisements, cartoons, drawings, and photographs.</p>

    <p><strong>Size:</strong> 1,700 periodical titles with 95,000 issues; 255 annual titles with 1,100 issues; 330 newspaper titles on 2,000 reels of film</p>
    <p><strong>Selection criteria:</strong> Annuals up to 1900, periodicals up to 1920, and newspapers up to 1930. The periodicals subset draws heavily on the Early Canadian Periodicals project, with guidance from an Advisory Committee.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Collection highlights</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>All annuals and periodicals microfilmed by the Canadian Institute for Historical Microreproductions (CIHM)</li>
      <li>All periodicals available on Early Canadiana Online (ECO)</li>
      <li>Serials recently added and not available on ECO or in the CIHM fiche collection</li>
      <li>Local, trade, religious, and student newspapers and journals; city directories and annual reports</li>
      <li>Specialized periodicals across literature, medicine, science and technology, education, agriculture, business, recreation and sports, politics, religion, history, law, military, music, genealogy, publishing, economics, fashion, philately, photography, humour, psychology, transportation, and more</li>
    </ul>

